      "created": "2013-10-10T22:27:22.631+0000",
      "description": "Currently, a container is considered done when its OS process exits. This makes it cumbersome for apps to be able to reuse containers for different processes. Long running daemons may want to run in the same containers as the previous versions. So eg. is an hbase region server crashes/upgraded it would want to restart in the same container where everything it needs would already be warm and ready.",
